    "faq": {
      "type": "brand-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the difference between a contact adhesive and PVA glue?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>Contact adhesives</strong> like Evo-Stik 528 bond immediately when two coated surfaces are pressed together, creating a high-strength instant bond. They are ideal for laminates, worktops and non-porous materials. <strong>PVA wood glue</strong> is a water-based adhesive that requires clamping while it dries and is best suited for porous materials like timber. Use contact adhesive when you need an immediate bond on non-porous surfaces, and PVA when you have time to clamp and are working with wood.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Which Evo-Stik tile adhesive should I use?",
            "answer": "<p>For standard ceramic wall tiles on plaster or plasterboard, Evo-Stik's <strong>ready-mixed wall tile adhesive</strong> is the simplest option. For floor tiles, porcelain, natural stone or exterior applications, use a <strong>cement-based flexible tile adhesive</strong> like the Rapid Set Floor & Wall range. In wet areas such as bathrooms and showers, choose a waterproof formulation and pair it with a <strong>mould-resistant grout</strong>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long do Evo-Stik adhesives take to dry?",
            "answer": "<p>Drying times vary by product. <strong>Evo-Stik Impact contact adhesive</strong> bonds immediately on contact after both surfaces have been coated and allowed to become touch-dry (typically 10-15 minutes). <strong>Rapid-set tile adhesives</strong> achieve initial set in approximately 2 hours and full cure within 24 hours. <strong>PVA wood glues</strong> typically require clamping for 1-2 hours with full strength reached after 24 hours. Always check the product technical data sheet for specific guidance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is Evo-Stik part of Bostik?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. <strong>Evo-Stik is a trademark of Bostik</strong>, one of the world's leading manufacturers of adhesives, sealants and building chemicals. Bostik is part of the <strong>Arkema Group</strong>, a global specialty chemicals company. The Evo-Stik brand is focused on the UK trade and DIY markets, with the majority of products manufactured in Bostik's own UK factories.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I use Evo-Stik products outdoors?",
            "answer": "<p>Many Evo-Stik products are suitable for exterior use. The <strong>Floor & Wall Tile Adhesive</strong> range includes waterproof formulations rated for interior and exterior applications. Evo-Stik also produces <strong>exterior wood adhesives</strong> and <strong>weatherproof sealants</strong>. Always check the product label — it will clearly state whether the product is suitable for exterior use.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you offer trade pricing on Evo-Stik?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. We offer <strong>competitive trade pricing</strong> across the full Evo-Stik range including contact adhesives, tile adhesives, sealants and grab adhesives. Contact our trade team on <strong>01843 593 440</strong> or email <strong>sales@invictatools.co.uk</strong> for volume discounts and trade account enquiries. Free next-day delivery on all orders over £99.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
